{{Quote|It's dismal. We've had to cancel over half of our planned activities due to small numbers. The redfish have actually reclaimed the northern beaches, they're so empty.|Byll Shotaleve|<ref name="HNN">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|52|business/13418_1.html|Leisure Industry Suffers Record Losses}}</ref>}}
'''Byll Shotaleve''' was a resort owner on<ref name="HNN" /> the popular vacation [[Planet/Legends|world]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|27|Amfar}}</ref> [[Amfar/Legends|Amfar]]. When the number of tourists dropped steeply<ref name="HNN" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="Date">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|52|business/13418_1.html|Leisure Industry Suffers Record Losses}} is set on the date 13:4:18, which corresponds to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] according to the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref> several [[Beach/Legends|beaches]] on Amfar were reclaimed by [[Redfish/Legends|redfish]]. In an interview published in the [[HoloNet News CoCo District Edition|CoCo District Edition]] of the [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]], Shotaleve expressed their discontent with having to cancel half their planned activities due to lack of attendance, as well as the return of redfish where resort-goers normally stayed.<ref name="HNN" />

==Behind the scenes==
Byll Shotaleve appeared in "Leisure Industry Suffers Record Losses," an article<ref name="HNN" /> written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]]<ref name="credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref> and published in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 52|''HoloNet News Vol. 531'' #52]] on the [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News website]]<ref name="HNN" /> on [[April 18]], [[2002]].<ref name="HNN52 date">{{JCFCite|url=posts/6493893|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|user=IAmTheDarkSide|date=2002-04-18|time=6:27 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220914072939/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-official-holonetnews-discussion-thread.5990764/page-11#post-6493893}}</ref>

